PI and Gmail — run completed at {{ $now.toFormat('HH:mm') }}","otherOptions":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.slack","typeVersion":2.3,"position":[5238,400],"id":"d35fba1c-8cb6-4a4c-a14c-06bb2209053f","name":"Send Summary to Slack","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000,"onError":"continueErrorOutput"},{"parameters":{"assignments":{"assignments":[{"id":"9166129e-64c9-4c81-ad82-7702feea3024","name":"failedNode","value":"={{ $json.error?.node?.name || 'unknown' }}","type":"string"},{"id":"5f435579-b0f8-43d3-8c97-d0ed757e88d9","name":"errorMessage","value":"={{ $json.error?.message || JSON.stringify($json).slice(0,200) }}","type":"string"},{"id":"5530a824-6547-4d7a-beae-35d087c30b42","name":"workflow","value":"={{ $workflow.name }}","type":"string"}]},"options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.set","typeVersion":3.4,"position":[4590,1420],"id":"1faede6b-fe02-4649-9c7d-b311658adbfc","name":"Capture Failure Context"},{"parameters":{"select":"channel","channelId":{"__rl":true,"mode":"name","value":"#trading","cachedResultName":"#trading"},"text":"=🚨 {{ $json.workflow }} failed at {{ $json.failedNode }}: {{ $json.errorMessage }}","otherOptions":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.slack","typeVersion":2.3,"position":[4914,1420],"id":"7d018d5d-b7e9-4e5c-a5c2-bff50388b873","name":"Escalate Failure to Slack","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000},{"parameters":{"content":"### Every Few Minutes\n\nStarts the workflow on a timer — every 5 min. No input data; downstream nodes fetch what they need.\n\nNext: Probe Endpoint A","width":280,"height":232,"color":5},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-330,520],"id":"3d718ee5-e0fb-9061-f8f1-e9e2d5e5bffc","name":"Note: Every Few Minutes"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Probe Endpoint A\n\nGET https://service-a.example.com/healthz — retries 3× with backoff on failure.\n\nNext: Combine Probe Results\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 API key / bearer for the target API","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-6,250],"id":"080ac418-3835-360b-2ed8-c70a28e1dbea","name":"Note: Probe Endpoint A"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Probe Endpoint B\n\nGET https://service-b.example.com/healthz — retries 3× with backoff on failure.\n\nNext: Combine Probe Results\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 API key / bearer for the target API","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[318,760],"id":"b573ea78-ba23-51f8-1d81-20b9f0bb62cb","name":"Note: Probe Endpoint B"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Probe Endpoint C\n\nGET https://service-c.example.com/healthz — retries 3× with backoff on failure.\n\nNext: Combine Probe Results\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 API key / bearer for the target API","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[642,1270],"id":"62c301d3-512d-fdcf-ebd0-0070889bd8e2","name":"Note: Probe Endpoint C"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Combine Probe Results\n\nRejoins 3 branches into one stream (mode: append) so downstream logic runs once.\n\nNext: All Healthy?","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1290,520],"id":"044b1240-06aa-2e8c-ff60-772da4f4400d","name":"Note: Combine Probe Results"},{"parameters":{"content":"### All Healthy?\n\nTwo-way gate on `={{ ($json.statusCode || 200) < 400 }}`. TRUE continues the happy path, FALSE takes the alternate branch.\n\nPorts: ①→ Record Uptime Metric · ②→ Already Alerted? (State Check)","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2262,520],"id":"dbaabc17-2acb-3133-d495-860f6ac096b0","name":"Note: All Healthy?"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Record Uptime Metric\n\ngoogleSheets — `append` operation against the connected account.\n\nPorts: ①→ Sort Assets Newest First · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2586,280],"id":"b607ae62-d582-cb07-c7cb-10e0719a8238","name":"Note: Record Uptime Metric"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Already Alerted? (State Check)\n\nCross-execution dedupe: remembers keys it has processed before and drops repeats — the idempotency guard.\n\nNext: Page On-Call via Slack","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2910,880],"id":"9b15ed26-ca92-7c43-f5e9-1426777ce86f","name":"Note: Already Alerted? (State Check)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Page On-Call via Slack\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3558,880],"id":"8af22ad2-c269-cd0f-380b-ffa8748b66ab","name":"Note: Page On-Call via Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Sort Assets Newest First\n\nOrders items (newest first) so limits and digests pick the most relevant records.\n\nNext: Cap Batch Volume","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4530,520],"id":"2800d9a0-fd4a-eafd-92e0-bc3f71ce11ab","name":"Note: Sort Assets Newest First"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Cap Batch Volume\n\nCaps the stream at 100 items to protect downstream quotas.\n\nNext: Send Summary to Slack","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4854,520],"id":"def8f1cc-5bb9-2b88-0152-de686ecd7bfa","name":"Note: Cap Batch Volume"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Send Summary to Slack\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5178,520],"id":"ec6460e8-da64-9847-05a8-7a48073fd2c5","name":"Note: Send Summary to Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Capture Failure Context\n\nShapes the item: writes `failedNode`, `errorMessage`, `workflow`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Escalate Failure to Slack","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4530,1540],"id":"eb8d6712-56d0-4e02-4a30-e71b43425c8d","name":"Note: Capture Failure Context"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Escalate Failure to Slack\n\nslack — `action` operation against the connected account.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4854,1540],"id":"91ef3174-d290-f1f6-3b8d-d01537331fed","name":"Note: Escalate Failure to Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"# Alert on a key metric with HTTP / REST API and Gmail\n\n**Pattern:** Threshold Monitoring · **Level:** Core · **Trigger:** Scheduled\n\n## What it does\nAlert on a key metric with HTTP / REST API and Gmail. It runs automatically on a schedule.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual portfolio tracking is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nEvery Few Minutes → Probe Endpoint A → Combine Probe Results → All Healthy? → Record Uptime Metric → Sort Assets Newest First → Cap Batch Volume → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to threshold monitoring without manual effort\n- Anyone automating portfolio tracking in finance\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Runs 24/7 in the background\n- Keeps your systems in sync\n- Improves response time\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: API key / bearer for the target API; Google OAuth2 / service account; Slack OAuth2.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.","width":480,"height":900},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-830,80],"id":"d1459681-5965-6044-7601-84829d5edbe2","name":"📘 Workflow Overview"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.","width":360,"height":260,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-230,-290],"id":"670609c1-8589-3998-3875-d92f98e43e54","name":"🛟 Error handling & retries"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🧹 Data quality\n\nDedupe/diff steps make re-runs safe: the same input twice will not create duplicate records. If you change the key fields, clear n8n's dedupe memory (node → 'Clear stored keys') before the next run.","width":360,"height":260,"color":1},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[190,-290],"id":"ff9119a7-4ace-6ad2-8802-4f33bd647ea7","name":"🧹 Data quality"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛠 Customize me\n\nQuick wins: point the data nodes at your own accounts (see 🔑 lines on each card), adjust the trigger cadence, and tune thresholds/labels to your portfolio tracking process. Every node card explains its role — safe to extend at any marked branch.","width":360,"height":260,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[610,-290],"id":"5d0dd498-d0f5-18f0-3350-dc45a683daba","name":"🛠 Customize me"}],"connections":{"Every Few Minutes":{"main":[[{"node":"Probe Endpoint A","type":"main","index":0},{"node":"Probe Endpoint B","type":"main","index":0},{"node":"Probe Endpoint C","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Probe Endpoint A":{"main":[[{"node":"Combine Probe Results","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Probe Endpoint B":{"main":[[{"node":"Combine Probe Results","type":"main","index":1}]]},"Probe Endpoint C":{"main":[[{"node":"Combine Probe Results","type":"main","index":2}]]},"Combine Probe Results":{"main":[[{"node":"All Healthy?","type":"main","index":0}]]},"All Healthy?":{"main":[[{"node":"Record Uptime Metric","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Already Alerted? (State Check)","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Already Alerted? (State Check)":{"main":[[{"node":"Page On-Call via Slack","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Record Uptime Metric":{"main":[[{"node":"Sort Assets Newest First","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Sort Assets Newest First":{"main":[[{"node":"Cap Batch Volume","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Cap Batch Volume":{"main":[[{"node":"Send Summary to Slack","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Capture Failure Context":{"main":[[{"node":"Escalate Failure to Slack","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Page On-Call via Slack":{"main":[[],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Send Summary to Slack":{"main":[[],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]}},"active":false,"settings":{"executionOrder":"v1"},"meta":{"templateCredsSetupCompleted":false},"tags":[],"pinData":{},"versionId":"18a8b191-cd5b-4b38-891b-976993de1109","id":"FDX08847"}